com.innowhere.jnieasy.core.typedec
Interface TypeNative

All Known Subinterfaces:
TypeCanBeNativeCapable, TypeNativeArray, TypeNativeBehavior, TypeNativeCapable, TypeNativeConstructor, TypeNativeFieldMethod, TypeNativeInstanceFieldMethod, TypeNativeInstanceMethod, TypeNativeLong, TypeNativeMethod, TypeNativeObject, TypeNativePointer, TypeNativePrimitive, TypeNativePrimitiveObject, TypeNativePrimitiveWrapper, TypeNativeStaticFieldMethod, TypeNativeStaticMethod, TypeNativeString, TypeNativeStringAnsi, TypeNativeStringBased, TypeNativeStringBuffer, TypeNativeStringBufferAnsi, TypeNativeStringBufferUnicode, TypeNativeStringUnicode
public interface TypeNative

The TypeNative is the interface that represents a native type declaration using native capable classes (user defined or predefined).

This native type must be seen as the type used in a C++ new sentence, it does not include any kind of "parameter pass/variable conventionalism" (by value or by pointer) used in C/C++ structure fields (and classes and unions) or formal parameters of methods.

Author:
Jose M. Arranz Santamaria
See Also:
VarTypeNative, NativeTypeManager.dec(Class)

Method Detail

size

long size()
Returns the size of the native memory of an instance of this native type.

If the type is a native string or a undefined length array, the size is unknown and an exception is thrown.

If primitive or primitive wrapper (e.g. NativeBoolean, NativeBooleanObject) the returned size is the Java size of the primitive type. This size is platform independent (e.g. boolean=1,char=2,int=4...) unless changed "per type instance" using NativeTypeManager.decPrimitive(Class,long) or globally using methods like NativeTypeManager.setDefaultBooleanSize(long).

Returns:
the size of the native memory of the type.
See Also:
NativeClassDescriptor.size()

preferredAlignSize

long preferredAlignSize()
Returns the preferred native alignment size of the native type, returns the alignment size of an instance of this native type.

This value is used to calculate the relative offsets of the fields of native structures, classes and unions, and may be replaced with a specificated field alignment or global structure alignment.

Native typeAlignment size
Primitive The alignment size is the "natural" alignment size of the Java primitive seen as JNI data type (e.g. jint), usually this value is the same as the memory size. May be changed "per type instance" with methods like NativeTypeManager.decPrimitive(Class,long,long) or globally using methods like NativeTypeManager.setDefaultBooleanSize(long,long).
Primitive wrappers (Integer etc) and native wrappers (NativeInteger etc) The alignment size of the wrapped primitive type
String, StringBuffer and wrappers The alignment size of the native char type used (1 if ANSI, the platform wchar_t size if UNICODE)
Structure, class or union The maximum alignment of fields
Array (normal, wrapper or user defined) The alignment size of the component type of the array
Pointer or user defined Pointer The pointer size of the platform
Method (all types) Undefined, an exception is thrown because memory size of the method is ever unknown and a method is never declared by value (the alignment size of a method field is ever the pointer size)

Returns:
the size of the preferred alignment size of the type.
See Also:
NativeClassDescriptor.alignSize(), NativeFieldStructureDescriptor.alignSize()
